<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>An Idea..</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Ragok">Ragok</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 9:38 a.m. 22/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> An Idea..<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I had posted this a few days ago, but i doubt many people had read my post so i will repost my idea.

<P>Mind you, this would need some experimenting with to see if it is viable, but here goes:
<BR>The level difference for grouping is dynamic, meaning at higher levels you can group with people more than the 5 level limit everyone gets used to at lower levels, and satill gain experience. The experience gain from defeating a monster therefore is dynamic also, meaning at higher levels monsters con at blue 3-4 levels lower, instead of just 1-2 like at lower levels. I would like to see the 4 level limit for pvp be dynamic also, meaning at level 30 you could go up against level 25's or level 37's. The exact limits (or curve) in how the level limit increases i am not sure of since i have no clue to the game code itself (verant would need to do this since one would need to understand the powercurve for levels).
<BR>Of course, as i stated above, this would need testing to see if someone out of the 4 level limit at higher levels is too easy or impossible to defeat in PvP. Also, this would only work if they tweak the spell resistance that is currently in place.
<P>This i think is a must, since as people advance in levels, the seperation (in levels) grows too since everyone advances at a different rate. It then could lead to a shortage of victims (or victimizers).
<P>Ragok Arnskull
<BR>skull@lvdi.net
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
